A typical interactive video will likely contain multiple text elements. This article takes a closer look at how these elements can be added to a scene or pop-up and configured.

## Add text elements
To add text element to the selected scene or pop-up:

- Open the **scene editor**.

- In the **sidebar**, go to **Text**.

- Click **Add text**.

A text element will be added to the timeline.

### Configure text elements
Click on the text element in the playback area or its timeline layer to open the settings:

- **Animation:** Select an animation style and when the animation should be displayed (in, out, in and out)

- **Text**

**Formatting:** Adjust the font, font size, and other formatting options for the text

- **Text:** Enter the text to be displayed on the screen

- **Duration:** Enter the exact timestamps to control the start and end of the element

- **Size and position:** Set the size and position of the image element and lock the aspect ratio

> Tip

The size and position of the element can also be adjusted in the playback area using intuitive drag-and-drop controls.

- **Box appearance:** Adjust the color filling of the image background, and configure the border of the image element

- **Delete:** Delete this element and its timeline layer
